SIMPLE: rugged
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rugged
<hw>Rug"ged</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Rug</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of asperities on the surface;
broken into sharp or irregular points, or otherwise uneven; not smooth;
rough; <as>as, a <ex>rugged</ex> mountain; a <ex>rugged</ex>
road</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>rugged</qex> bark of some broad elm.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not neat or regular; uneven.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His well-proportioned beard made rough and <qex>rugged</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Rough with bristles or hair; shaggy.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>rugged</xex> Russian bear.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Harsh; hard; crabbed; austere; -- said of temper,
character, and the like, or of persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither melt nor endear him, but leave him as hard,
<qex>rugged</qex>, and unconcerned as ever.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Stormy; turbulent; tempestuous; rude.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Rough to the ear; harsh; grating; -- said of sound,
style, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Through the harsh cadence of a <qex>rugged</qex> line.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Sour; surly; frowning; wrinkled; -- said of looks,
etc.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sleek o'er your <xex>rugged</xex> looks.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>Violent; rude; boisterrous; -- said of conduct,
manners, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>9.</sn> <def>Vigorous; robust; hardy; -- said of health,
physique, etc.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Rough; uneven; wrinkled; cragged; coarse; rude;
harsh; hard; crabbed; severe; austere; surly; sour; frowning; violent;
boisterous; tumultuous; turbulent; stormy; tempestuous;
inclement.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rug"ged*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Rug"ged*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rugging</ent>⟦br⟧
